commits+pushes.\n320\t\t// Atomicity (no interleaving with other writes) is guaranteed by the implementation:\n321\t\t// - gitClient (local-disk): sync.Mutex around the whole sequence.\n322\t\t// - gitRestGitClientAdapter: relies on per-task serialization (Kafka partitioning by task_id).\n323\t\t// modify must return the new file bytes or an error.\n324\t\t// If modify returns an error, the file is not written and no commit is made.\n325\t\tAtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush(\n326\t\t\tctx context.Context,\n327\t\t\tabsPath string,\n328\t\t\tmodify func(current []byte) ([]byte, error),\n329\t\t\tmessage string,\n330\t\t) error\n331\t\t// Path returns the local clone path.\n332\t\tPath() string\n333\t\t// ListFiles returns relative file paths under the repo root matching the single-level\n334\t\t// glob pattern (e.g. \"tasks/*.md\"). Paths are relative to the repo root.\n335\t\tListFiles(ctx context.Context, glob string) ([]string, error)\n336\t\t// ReadFile reads the file at relPath (relative to repo root, e.g. \"tasks/foo.md\")\n337\t\t// and returns its content.\n338\t\tReadFile(ctx context.Context, relPath string) ([]byte, error)\n339\t\t// WriteFile writes content to relPath (relative to repo root) on local disk."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_5jclw9a5ulel_1","session_id":"d24d929e-901e-43de-a918-963fd3b15361","uuid":"d01daae2-6e57-4262-9815-8857ee06ca8e","timestamp":"2026-06-30T09:40:41.295Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","task_description":"Generate dark-factory prompts from spec"}
