{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T4CX5GKxF7Z5WngLvKnYHN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Period-Token Semantics\n2\t\n3\tThe recurrence kind is NOT carried in task frontmatter. Decrement is inferred from the period-token suffix shape in the task title. This table is the durable contract between `bborbe/recurring-task-creator` (the publisher that stamps tokens) and `bborbe/agent-task-controller` (the consumer that decrements them for auto-supersede).\n4\t\n5\tToken shapes and firing rules are defined in the Obsidian KB page [[Per-Kind Firing Semantics for Recurring Task Schedulers]]. This document adds the **decrement direction** — the arithmetic that maps a new instance's token to the prior period's token — which the KB page does not cover.\n6\t\n7\t## Decrement Table\n8\t\n9\t| Recurrence kind | Period-token shape (new) | Prior-token shape | Decrement rule |\n10\t|---|---|---|---|\n11\t| Daily | `YYYY-MM-DD` | `YYYY-MM-DD` | one calendar day before the new instance's token date |\n12\t| Weekday (list) | `YYYYWww-<3-letter-abbrev>` | `YYYYWww-<same abbrev>` | one ISO week before; weekday suffix preserved (e.g. `2026W27-sat` → `2026W26-sat`) |\n13\t| Weekly | `YYYYWww` (e.g. `2026W27`) | `YYYYWww` | one ISO week before (e.g. `2026W27` → `2026W26`) |\n14\t| Monthly | `YYYY-MM` | `YYYY-MM` | one calendar month before (e.g. `2026-06` → `2026-05`) |\n15\t| Quarterly | `YYYYQq` (e.g. `2026Q2`) | `YYYYQq` | one quarter before (e.g. `2026Q2` → `2026Q1`); wrap to prior year at `Q1` → `Q4` |\n16\t| Yearly | `YYYY` | `YYYY` | one calendar year before (e.g. `2026` → `2025`) |\n17\t\n18\t## Shape Recognition Order\n19\t\n20\tThe hook identifies the kind by matching the suffix against these shapes in order:\n21\t\n22\t1. Daily (`YYYY-MM-DD`)\n23\t2. Weekday (`YYYYWww-abc`)\n24\t3. Weekly (`YYYYWww`)\n25\t4. Monthly (`YYYY-MM`)\n26\t5. Quarterly (`YYYYQq`)\n27\t6. Yearly (`YYYY`)\n28\t\n29\tIf no shape matches, the hook logs a warning and is a no-op (non-recurring or unrecognized title).\n30\t\n31\t## Boundary Cases\n32\t\n33\tDecrement must handle period boundaries correctly:\n34\t\n35\t- **Quarterly year-boundary**: `2026Q1 → 2025Q4` (wraps to prior year)\n36\t- **Weekly ISO-week-boundary**: `2026W01 → 2025W52` (wraps to prior year)\n37\t- **Monthly year-boundary**: `2026-01 → 2025-12` (wraps to prior year)\n38\t- **Daily year-boundary**: `2026-01-01 → 2025-12-31` (wraps to prior year)\n39\t\n40\tISO-week and weekday arithmetic uses the Go `time` package's ISO-week helpers; the decrement must produce the same canonical token shape the publisher would have produced for the prior period.\n41\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_5jclw9a5ulel_1","session_id":"d24d929e-901e-43de-a918-963fd3b15361","uuid":"a28d7636-ace8-452c-af54-9355c4f5bf9c","timestamp":"2026-06-30T09:42:01.361Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","task_description":"Generate dark-factory prompts from spec"}
