{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZX57cBwWiBHf8UiyMiVPE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: completed\n3\tspec: [001-scanner-auto-inject-flag]\n4\tsummary: Added required AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER env flag to application config, plumbed boolean into vaultScanner constructors\n5\texecution_id: agent-task-controller-scanner-flag-exec-001-spec-001-config-and-factory-wiring\n6\tdark-factory-version: v0.187.10-3-g508361f-dirty\n7\tcreated: \"2026-06-28T00:00:00Z\"\n8\tqueued: \"2026-06-27T22:36:59Z\"\n9\tstarted: \"2026-06-27T22:37:00Z\"\n10\tcompleted: \"2026-06-27T22:43:51Z\"\n11\t---\n12\t\n13\t<summary>\n14\t\n15\t- The controller now refuses to start when the new required deployment-time auto-inject flag is not set in the environment, so a misconfigured pod crash-loops instead of silently re-introducing the dual-writer race.\n16\t- A single boolean config decides whether this replica is allowed to backfill missing or invalid task identifiers; the value is plumbed from config into the vault scanner so a later prompt can gate the three injection sites on it.\n17\t- Existing required env vars and existing factory wiring for the command consumer remain unchanged.\n18\t- Existing scanner constructor call sites in tests are updated mechanically to pass the new boolean — this is in scope because the spec explicitly allows factory signatures to grow a new parameter.\n19\t- No production behavior change at runtime when the flag is `true`; parity with today is the regression bar.\n20\t\n21\t</summary>\n22\t\n23\t<objective>\n24\t\n25\tIntroduce a required `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` env flag on the `application` config, parse it once at startup so a missing/unparseable value aborts the process before any scan runs, and plumb the resulting boolean into the vault scanner as a private field via a new constructor parameter. When the flag parses to `true`, behavior is identical to today; the gate logic at the three injection sites is added by prompt 2.\n26\t\n27\t</objective>\n28\t\n29\t<context>\n30\t\n31\tRead `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` for project conventions.\n32\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-patterns.md` for interface + constructor conventions.\n33\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-error-wrapping-guide.md` for `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)` usage (never `fmt.Errorf`).\n34\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-testing-guide.md` for the Ginkgo/Gomega test layout.\n35\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-precommit.md` for file-level lint limits.\n36\t\n37\tRead `/workspace/main.go` end-to-end. The `application` struct (lines 48-64) holds env-driven config parsed by the `github.com/bborbe/argument/v2` library. The scanner is constructed at line 106 via `scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(gitClient, a.TaskDir, a.PollInterval, trigger, metrics.New())`.\n38\t\n39\tRead `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go` end-to-end. The two public constructors are `NewVaultScanner` (line 98) and `NewGitRestVaultScanner` (line 119). Both currently take five parameters: `gitClient gitclient.GitClient, taskDir string, pollInterval time.Duration, trigger <-chan struct{}, m metrics.Metrics`. Both return the `VaultScanner` interface and both build a `&vaultScanner{...}` struct literal internally (lines 105 and 126). The struct definition is at lines 54-62.\n40\t\n41\tRead `/workspace/main_internal_test.go` end-to-end. It demonstrates the pattern for reflecting on `application{}` field tags (`TestApplicationVaultNameFieldExists` at line 59 is the closest template — same `required:\"true\"` shape).\n42\t\n43\tRead `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner_test.go` lines 185, 502, 511, 531, 547, 947 — these are the six existing call sites of `scanner.NewVaultScanner` / `scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner` in tests. They will each gain `true` as the new final argument (one-line mechanical edit).\n44\t\n45\tRead `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner_internal_test.go` line 39 — the only `&vaultScanner{...}` struct-literal in any test file (the external `_test` file at `vault_scanner_test.go` is `package scanner_test` and cannot access the unexported struct, so the literal cannot exist there). This literal gains `autoInject: true`.\n46\t\n47\tRead `/workspace/pkg/factory/factory.go` end-to-end. It currently only contains `CreateCommandConsumer`. This prompt does NOT add a factory function for the scanner — see Requirement 3 for why the constructor-parameter approach is used instead.\n48\t\n49\tLibrary note: `github.com/bborbe/argument/v2`'s `validateRequiredField` treats `case bool:` as a no-op (a `required:\"true\"` bool always passes validation because Go's zero value is `false`, and the env parser uses `strconv.ParseBool` which silently maps unset → `false`). The field MUST therefore be declared as `string` with `required:\"true\"`, parsed once via `strconv.ParseBool` at the start of `Run()`, with an explicit error when parsing fails.\n50\t\n51\t</context>\n52\t\n53\t<requirements>\n54\t\n55\t1. **Add the required env field to `application` in `/workspace/main.go`.**\n56\t   - Field name: `AutoInjectTaskIdentifier`.\n57\t   - Type: `string` (NOT `bool` — see the library note in `<context>`; `required:\"true\"` on a bool is silently bypassed).\n58\t   - Struct tag (preserve the column alignment of the surrounding fields):\n59\t     ```\n60\t     AutoInjectTaskIdentifier string `required:\"true\"  arg:\"auto-inject-task-identifier\" env:\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\" usage:\"allow this replica to backfill missing/invalid task_identifier fields (set true on exactly one replica per shared vault; false on all others); required\"`\n61\t     ```\n62\t   - Place the field after `VaultName` (currently the last field) so config grouping stays clean.\n63\t   - Do NOT add a `default:` tag. Spec Non-goals bullet (verbatim quote): *\"Do NOT add a default value for `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` — a default IS the regression we're preventing\"*.\n64\t\n65\t2. **Parse the flag once at the start of `Run()` in `/workspace/main.go`.**\n66\t   - Insert immediately after `routing.ValidateVaultName(...)` at line 68 and BEFORE `libmetrics.NewBuildInfoMetrics().SetBuildInfo(...)` at line 71:\n67\t     ```go\n68\t     autoInject, err := strconv.ParseBool(a.AutoInjectTaskIdentifier)\n69\t     if err != nil {\n70\t         return errors.Errorf(\n71\t             ctx,\n72\t             \"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER must be parseable as bool (true/false), got %q\",\n73\t             a.AutoInjectTaskIdentifier,\n74\t         )\n75\t     }\n76\t     ```\n77\t   - Add `\"strconv\"` to the stdlib import block (alphabetical position between `\"os\"` and `\"time\"`).\n78\t   - `errors` (`github.com/bborbe/errors`) is already imported — reuse it.\n79\t   - This single parsed `autoInject` value is passed to the scanner constructor in Requirement 5.\n80\t\n81\t3. **Extend the two public scanner constructors with `autoInject bool` as a new trailing parameter.**\n82\t   - Spec Constraints bullet (verbatim quote): *\"Existing factory signatures in `pkg/factory/factory.go` may grow a new parameter but must not lose existing parameters.\"* The same additive-signature rule is applied here to `NewVaultScanner` / `NewGitRestVaultScanner` because that is the minimal idiomatic Go change (a construction-time mutator on the public interface would pollute the API with a one-caller setter and force a counterfeiter regen).\n83\t   - In `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`:\n84\t     - Change `NewVaultScanner` signature to:\n85\t       ```go\n86\t       func NewVaultScanner(\n87\t           gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n88\t           taskDir string,\n89\t           pollInterval time.Duration,\n90\t           trigger <-chan struct{},\n91\t           m metrics.Metrics,\n92\t           autoInject bool,\n93\t       ) VaultScanner {\n94\t       ```\n95\t     - Change `NewGitRestVaultScanner` signature identically (same new trailing `autoInject bool`).\n96\t     - In both constructor bodies, set `autoInject: autoInject` on the returned `&vaultScanner{...}` literal.\n97\t\n98\t4. **Add the private `autoInject` field to the `vaultScanner` struct.**\n99\t   - In `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`, add `autoInject bool` as the last field of the struct (after `ops fileOps` at line 61):\n100\t     ```go\n101\t     type vaultScanner struct {\n102\t         gitClient    gitclient.GitClient\n103\t         taskDir      string\n104\t         pollInterval time.Duration\n105\t         hashes       map[string]fileEntry\n106\t         trigger      <-chan struct{}\n107\t         metrics      metrics.Metrics\n108\t         ops          fileOps\n109\t         autoInject   bool\n110\t     }\n111\t     ```\n112\t   - Do NOT add any method on `*vaultScanner` for this field — it is set at construction time. The gate logic in `processFile` is added by prompt 2.\n113\t   - Do NOT add `autoInject` to the public `VaultScanner` interface — it is a private construction parameter, not a public capability.\n114\t   - Do NOT regenerate `/workspace/mocks/vault_scanner.go` — the public interface (`Run`, `RunCycle`) is unchanged, so the existing counterfeiter mock is still valid.\n115\t\n116\t5. **Update the scanner construction in `/workspace/main.go` (line 106) to pass `autoInject`.**\n117\t   - Replace:\n118\t     ```go\n119\t     scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(\n120\t         gitClient,\n121\t         a.TaskDir,\n122\t         a.PollInterval,\n123\t         trigger,\n124\t         metrics.New(),\n125\t     ),\n126\t     ```\n127\t     with:\n128\t     ```go\n129\t     scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(\n130\t         gitClient,\n131\t         a.TaskDir,\n132\t         a.PollInterval,\n133\t         trigger,\n134\t         metrics.New(),\n135\t         autoInject,\n136\t     ),\n137\t     ```\n138\t   - The five existing arguments stay in the same order; `autoInject` is the new trailing arg.\n139\t\n140\t6. **Update the six existing scanner-constructor call sites in `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner_test.go` to pass `true`.**\n141\t   - The call sites are at approximately lines 185, 502, 511, 531, 547, 947. Use `grep -n 'NewVaultScanner\\|NewGitRestVaultScanner' pkg/scanner/vault_scanner_test.go` to find them mechanically.\n142\t   - For each call, append `, true` as the new last argument. Example:\n143\t     - Before: `scanner.NewVaultScanner(fakeGit, taskDir, time.Hour, nil, metrics.New())`\n144\t     - After:  `scanner.NewVaultScanner(fakeGit, taskDir, time.Hour, nil, metrics.New(), true)`\n145\t   - All six call sites exercise the existing inject behavior, so `true` is the correct value (parity with today).\n146\t   - This per-call-site update IS in scope — see the spec constraint quoted in Requirement 3.\n147\t\n148\t7. **Update the one `&vaultScanner{...}` struct literal in `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner_internal_test.go` (line 39) to add `autoInject: true`.**\n149\t   - Verify there is only one such literal in any test file by running `grep -rn '&vaultScanner{' pkg/scanner/` — the external `vault_scanner_test.go` is `package scanner_test` and cannot access the unexported struct, so no literal exists there.\n150\t   - Add `autoInject: true,` as a new key inside the `&vaultScanner{...}` literal (the existing fields are `metrics:` and `ops:`).\n151\t\n152\t8. **Add a reflection-based field assertion test in `/workspace/main_internal_test.go`.**\n153\t   - Append (do NOT modify existing tests) a new test mirroring `TestApplicationVaultNameFieldExists` (line 59):\n154\t     ```go\n155\t     func TestApplicationAutoInjectTaskIdentifierFieldExists(t *testing.T) {\n156\t         typ := reflect.TypeOf(application{})\n157\t         f, ok := typ.FieldByName(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier\")\n158\t         if !ok {\n159\t             t.Fatalf(\"application struct is missing AutoInjectTaskIdentifier field\")\n160\t         }\n161\t         if f.Type.Kind() != reflect.String {\n162\t             t.Fatalf(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier must be string (required:\\\"true\\\" on bool is silently bypassed by the argument library), got %s\", f.Type.Kind())\n163\t         }\n164\t         if got, want := f.Tag.Get(\"env\"), \"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\"; got != want {\n165\t             t.Errorf(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier env tag = %q, want %q\", got, want)\n166\t         }\n167\t         if got, want := f.Tag.Get(\"arg\"), \"auto-inject-task-identifier\"; got != want {\n168\t             t.Errorf(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier arg tag = %q, want %q\", got, want)\n169\t         }\n170\t         if got, want := f.Tag.Get(\"required\"), \"true\"; got != want {\n171\t             t.Errorf(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier required tag = %q, want %q\", got, want)\n172\t         }\n173\t         if got := f.Tag.Get(\"default\"); got != \"\" {\n174\t             t.Errorf(\"AutoInjectTaskIdentifier default tag = %q, want empty (no default per spec Non-goals)\", got)\n175\t         }\n176\t     }\n177\t     ```\n178\t\n179\t9. **Add a Ginkgo test that calls the real `argument.Parse` to verify the `required:\"true\"` boundary.**\n180\t   - File: `/workspace/main_test.go` is currently the `TestSuite` bootstrap in `package main_test`. Add a NEW test file `/workspace/main_argument_parse_test.go` in `package main_test` (do NOT modify `main_test.go`).\n181\t   - Purpose: exercise the actual `github.com/bborbe/argument/v2` library validator against the `application` struct with `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` unset, asserting that parsing returns a non-nil error referencing the env var name. This covers AC1 at the real library boundary (the reflection test in Requirement 8 only covers struct shape; this one exercises the parser).\n182\t   - Skeleton:\n183\t     ```go\n184\t     package main_test\n185\t\n186\t     import (\n187\t         \"context\"\n188\t         \"os\"\n189\t\n190\t         libargument \"github.com/bborbe/argument/v2\"\n191\t         . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n192\t         . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n193\t\n194\t         pkgmain \"github.com/bborbe/agent-task-controller\"\n195\t     )\n196\t     ```\n197\t     Note: the `application` struct is unexported (`package main`). The test cannot import it directly. Instead, declare a local struct in the test that pins the same `env:\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\"` + `required:\"true\"` shape, then assert the library returns a non-nil error when the env var is unset:\n198\t     ```go\n199\t     var _ = Describe(\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER required-tag enforcement (AC1)\", func() {\n200\t         type appShape struct {\n201\t             AutoInjectTaskIdentifier string `required:\"true\" arg:\"auto-inject-task-identifier\" env:\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\" usage:\"x\"`\n202\t         }\n203\t\n204\t         var saved string\n205\t         var hadValue bool\n206\t\n207\t         BeforeEach(func() {\n208\t             saved, hadValue = os.LookupEnv(\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\")\n209\t             Expect(os.Unsetenv(\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\")).To(Succeed())\n210\t             // Also clear the CLI arg path: argument library reads os.Args; tests run with `go test` args only.\n211\t         })\n212\t\n213\t         AfterEach(func() {\n214\t             if hadValue {\n215\t                 Expect(os.Setenv(\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\", saved)).To(Succeed())\n216\t             }\n217\t         })\n218\t\n219\t         It(\"returns a non-nil error from argument.Parse when the env var is unset\", func() {\n220\t             var app appShape\n221\t             err := libargument.Parse(context.Background(), &app)\n222\t             Expect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n223\t             Expect(err.Error()).To(ContainSubstring(\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\"))\n224\t         })\n225\t     })\n226\t     ```\n227\t   - Drop the `pkgmain` import if unused. Confirm the correct argument-library import path by running `grep -rn 'github.