anged after the six call-site edits in Requirement 6 and the one struct-literal edit in Requirement 7 (all pass `true` / `autoInject: true`).\n242\t- Spec Constraints bullet (verbatim quote): *\"Existing factory signatures in `pkg/factory/factory.go` may grow a new parameter but must not lose existing parameters.\"* — `CreateCommandConsumer` keeps all eight existing parameters unchanged.\n243\t- Per `go-error-wrapping-guide.md`: errors wrap with `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)` (never `fmt.Errorf`).\n244\t- Per `go-precommit.md`: file-level lint limits (funlen 80, nestif 4, golines 100) apply. The `Run()` function already carries `//nolint:funlen` at line 66 — adding the 7-line parse block stays within tolerance; do not remove the existing nolint directive.\n245\t- Do NOT commit — dark-factory handles git.\n246\t- All existing tests in `/workspace` must still pass after this prompt's changes.\n247\t\n248\t</constraints>\n249\t\n250\t<verification>\n251\t\n252\tRun iteratively while implementing (fast feedback):\n253\t\n254\t```\n255\tcd /workspace && go build ./...\n256\tcd /workspace && go test ./pkg/scanner/... -v\n257\tcd /workspace && go test ./... -run TestApplication -v\n258\t```\n259\t\n260\tRun ONCE at the end:\n261\t\n262\t```\n263\tcd /workspace && make precommit\n264\t```\n265\t\n266\tExpected new test names in `go test -v` output (AC1):\n267\t- `TestApplicationAutoInjectTaskIdentifierFieldExists`\n268\t- `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER required-tag enforcement (AC1) > returns a non-nil error from argument.Parse when the env var is unset`\n269\t\n270\t</verification>\n271\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_5jclw9a5ulel_1","session_id":"d24d929e-901e-43de-a918-963fd3b15361","uuid":"7acc77a7-ff06-498b-a4e7-e5cf4865a07c","timestamp":"2026-06-30T09:42:15.932Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","task_description":"Generate dark-factory prompts from spec"}
