{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MSGadTd6aoo7uihsjsUXZA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tspec: [\"002\"]\n3\tstatus: draft\n4\tcreated: \"2026-06-30T10:00:00Z\"\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\t<summary>\n8\t\n9\t- After the controller writes a new recurring-task instance, it now automatically transitions the prior period's instance from `in_progress` to `aborted` — closing the manual close-out tax for inbox-style recurring tasks.\n10\t- The supersede runs only for instances the recurring-task publisher created and only when the new instance is NOT flagged audit-style; audit-style instances (`check-prometheus-alerts`, `ibkr-swing-trading`) are deliberately left untouched so a missed firing stays visible.\n11\t- The prior file is stamped `status: aborted`, `phase: done`, a completion timestamp, and a `superseded_by` back-pointer to the new instance — all other frontmatter and the body are preserved.\n12\t- The behavior is safe under Kafka redelivery (a prior already aborted/completed is a no-op) and never fails the create flow: any read/parse/write problem is logged at WARNING and swallowed because the new instance is already on disk.\n13\t- Operators can confirm activity by grepping git log for `auto-supersede prior recurring task` and pod logs for `auto-supersede:`.\n14\t- A crafted title that would produce a path-separator-bearing prior path is rejected (no-op + WARNING), preventing path traversal.\n15\t\n16\t</summary>\n17\t\n18\t<objective>\n19\t\n20\tExtend the `create-task` executor so that, immediately after a successful new-instance write, it supersedes the prior-period instance for the same Schedule: read the prior file, and if it exists and is still `in_progress` and the new instance is not audit-style and was created by the recurring-task publisher, transition it to `aborted` via a read-modify-write that preserves all other content. Wire the new dependency (clock) through the factory. The supersede must never cause the handler to return an error.\n21\t\n22\t</objective>\n23\t\n24\t<context>\n25\t\n26\tRead `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` for project conventions.\n27\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-patterns.md`, `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-error-wrapping-guide.md`, `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-testing-guide.md`, and `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-time-injection.md` (clock injection via `libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter`, `SetNow()` in tests).\n28\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-factory-pattern.md` for zero-logic factory wiring.\n29\t\n30\tRead `/workspace/docs/period-token-semantics.md` — the contract prompt 1 implements.\n31\t\n32\tRead `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor.go` IN FULL. The frozen insertion point is inside `NewCreateTaskExecutor`'s handler func, immediately after the successful `gitClient.AtomicWriteAndCommitPush(...)` call (currently lines 100-112) and BEFORE the final `return nil, nil, nil` (line 115). Note these existing helpers in the same file you will reuse:\n33\t- `resolveCreateTaskRelPath(ctx, taskDir, cmd)` (line 126) — already rejects titles containing `/` or `\\`.\n34\t- `isNotFoundReadError(err)` (line 160) — returns true when a `gitClient.ReadFile` error embeds `returned 404`. Reuse this verbatim for the prior-file not-found check.\n35\t- `marshalFileContent(ctx, fm, body)` (in `task_increment_frontmatter_executor.go` line 145) — marshals `lib.TaskFrontmatter` + body back to file bytes.\n36\t- `parseTaskFrontmatter(frontmatterStr)` (in `task_increment_frontmatter_executor.go` line 119) — YAML-unmarshals a frontmatter string into `lib.TaskFrontmatter`.\n37\t\n38\tRead `/workspace/pkg/command/task_update_frontmatter_executor.go` IN FULL — this is the canonical read-modify-write pattern. `buildUpdateModifyFn` (lines 95-125) shows the exact `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush` modify-closure shape: extract frontmatter via `result.ExtractFrontmatter(ctx, current)`, extract body via `result.ExtractBody(ctx, current)`, parse via `parseTaskFrontmatter`, mutate the `lib.TaskFrontmatter` map, return `marshalFileContent(ctx, fm, body)`. Mirror this for the supersede write.\n39\t\n40\tRead `/workspace/pkg/gitrestclient/git_rest_client.go` lines 298-345 for the `GitClient` interface. The two methods you call:\n41\t- `ReadFile(ctx context.Context, relPath string) ([]byte, error)` — relPath is repo-root-relative (e.g. `tasks/foo.md`).\n42\t- `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush(ctx context.Context, absPath string, modify func(current []byte) ([]byte, error), message string) error` — absPath is `filepath.Join(gitClient.Path(), relPath)`.\n43\t\n44\tRead `/workspace/pkg/result/result_writer.go` lines 352-390 — `ExtractFrontmatter(ctx, content) (string, error)` and `ExtractBody(ctx, content) (string, error)` (package `result`, import alias already used as `\"github.com/bborbe/agent-task-controller/pkg/result\"`).\n45\t\n46\tRead `/workspace/pkg/factory/factory.go` IN FULL. `CreateCommandConsumer` (line 21) wires `command.NewCreateTaskExecutor(gitClient, taskDir, vaultName)` at line 35. You will add a `currentDateTime libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter` parameter to both `NewCreateTaskExecutor` and `CreateCommandConsumer` and thread it through.\n47\t\n48\tRead `/workspace/main.go` lines 110-160. `currentDateTime := libtime.NewCurrentDateTime()` is created at line 112 and already passed to `publisher.NewTaskPublisher(...)` (line 124) and `result.NewResultWriter(...)` (line 151). The `factory.CreateCommandConsumer(...)` call is at line 152 — you will pass `currentDateTime` into it.\n49\t\n50\tClock contract (verified in repo): `libtime \"github.com/bborbe/time\"`; the getter type is `libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter`; usage is `currentDateTime.Now()` returning a value whose `.UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)` yields an RFC 3339 timestamp (see `result_writer.go` line 304: `r.currentDateTime.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)`). Follow this exact idiom for `completed_date` — it satisfies the spec's \"full RFC 3339 timestamp\" Constraint.\n51\t\n52\tRead `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor_test.go` lines 1-160 for the Ginkgo test harness: `package command_test`, `mocks.GitClient` with `PathReturns`, `AtomicWriteAndCommitPushStub`, `ReadFileReturns`, `ReadFileReturnsOnCall`, and the `buildCmdObj(task.CreateCommand)` helper. New tests extend this same `Describe`.\n53\t\n54\tRead `/workspace/mocks/git_client.go` to confirm the counterfeiter mock exposes `ReadFileReturns`, `ReadFileReturnsOnCall`, `ReadFileCallCount`, `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushStub`, `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushReturns`, `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount`, and `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushArgsForCall` — you rely on these in tests. (The mock already exists; the `GitClient` interface is unchanged by this prompt, so NO counterfeiter regen is needed.)\n55\t\n56\tDEPENDENCY: prompt 1 must already have shipped `decrementRecurringTaskTitle` and the `DecrementRecurringTaskTitle` test seam in `pkg/command/`. If `grep -rn \"func decrementRecurringTaskTitle\" /workspace/pkg/command/` returns no match, STOP and report `status: failed` with message `\"period-token decrementor not yet deployed (prompt 1)\"` — do NOT re-implement it here.\n57\t\n58\t</context>\n59\t\n60\t<requirements>\n61\t\n62\t1. **Add the clock parameter to `NewCreateTaskExecutor` in `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor.go`.**\n63\t   - Add the import `libtime \"github.com/bborbe/time\"` to the import block.\n64\t   - Change the signature from:\n65\t     ```go\n66\t     func NewCreateTaskExecutor(\n67\t         gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n68\t         taskDir string,\n69\t         vaultName string,\n70\t     ) cdb.CommandObjectExecutorTx {\n71\t     ```\n72\t     to:\n73\t     ```go\n74\t     func NewCreateTaskExecutor(\n75\t         gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n76\t         taskDir string,\n77\t         vaultName string,\n78\t         currentDateTime libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter,\n79\t     ) cdb.CommandObjectExecutorTx {\n80\t     ```\n81\t   - This is the ONLY new constructor parameter (spec Constraint: \"no new constructor parameter beyond what is needed to inject the supersede helper... a clock for `completed_date`\").\n82\t\n83\t2. **Insert the supersede call at the frozen insertion point.** In the handler func, immediately after the successful `AtomicWriteAndCommitPush` block (after line 112's closing brace, after the existing `glog.V(2).Infof(\"create-task: created task file...\")` at lines 113-114) and BEFORE `return nil, nil, nil` (line 115), add:\n84\t   ```go\n85\t   supersedePriorRecurringTask(ctx, gitClient, taskDir, currentDateTime, cmd, relPath)\n86\t   ```\n87\t   The function returns nothing (errors are swallowed internally) so the handler's existing `return nil, nil, nil` is unchanged. The handler MUST still return `nil, nil, nil` on the success path (spec DB8).\n88\t\n89\t3. **Implement `supersedePriorRecurringTask` in `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor.go`** (or a new file `/workspace/pkg/command/task_supersede.go` in `package command` if the executor file would exceed ~250 lines — your choice, same package). Signature:\n90\t   ```go\n91\t   // supersedePriorRecurringTask transitions the prior-period recurring-task instance\n92\t   // to status: aborted after a new instance is materialized. It is a best-effort\n93\t   // hook: every failure path (ineligible, no prior, read/parse/write error) is logged\n94\t   // and swallowed so the already-written new instance is never rolled back.\n95\t   // newRelPath is the repo-root-relative path of the just-written new instance\n96\t   // (used as the superseded_by back-pointer).\n97\t   func supersedePriorRecurringTask(\n98\t       ctx context.Context,\n99\t       gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n100\t       taskDir string,\n101\t       currentDateTime libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter,\n102\t       cmd task.CreateCommand,\n103\t       newRelPath string,\n104\t   )\n105\t   ```\n106\t   Body logic, in order:\n107\t\n108\t   a. **Eligibility gate (spec DB1).** Read `created_by` and `audit_style` from `cmd.Frontmatter` (type `lib.TaskFrontmatter`, a `map[string]any`):\n109\t      - `createdBy, _ := cmd.Frontmatter.String(\"created_by\")` — if `createdBy != \"recurring-task-creator\"`, return (no-op, no log needed beyond V(3)).\n110\t      - For `audit_style`: read it tolerantly. `cmd.Frontmatter` is `map[string]any`; a YAML/JSON bool may arrive as `bool` or as the string `\"true\"`. Implement a small inline check: `if v, ok := cmd.Frontmatter[\"audit_style\"]; ok { if b, isBool := v.(bool); isBool && b { return }; if s, isStr := v.(string); isStr && s == \"true\" { return } }`. Absent or any other value → treat as `false` (eligible). Spec Constraint: \"absence is treated as `false`\".\n111\t\n112\t   b. **Compute prior title.** Derive the new instance's title. The new instance was written at `relPath` = `<taskDir>/<title>.md` (when the title path was used) — but to get the raw title robustly, use `cmd.Title` directly (the `task.CreateCommand` carries `Title`; confirm the field exists by reading the struct usage in `resolveCreateTaskRelPath` which references `cmd.Title`). Call:\n113\t      ```go\n114\t      priorTitle, err := decrementRecurringTaskTitle(ctx, cmd.Title)\n115\t      if err != nil {\n116\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: cannot decrement title %q for %s: %v\", cmd.Title, cmd.TaskIdentifier, err)\n117\t          return\n118\t      }\n119\t      ```\n120\t      Note: the WARNING for an unrecognized period-token shape (spec Failure Mode \"Period-token shape unrecognized\") is emitted here.\n121\t\n122\t   c. **Path-traversal defense (spec Security).** Reject a computed prior title that contains a path separator:\n123\t      ```go\n124\t      if strings.ContainsAny(priorTitle, \"/\\\\\") {\n125\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: computed prior title %q contains path separator; skipping for %s\", priorTitle, cmd.TaskIdentifier)\n126\t          return\n127\t      }\n128\t      ```\n129\t      Then build the prior relative path: `priorRelPath := filepath.Join(taskDir, priorTitle+\".md\")`.\n130\t\n131\t   d. **Read the prior file (spec DB3).**\n132\t      ```go\n133\t      content, err := gitClient.ReadFile(ctx, priorRelPath)\n134\t      if err != nil {\n135\t          if isNotFoundReadError(err) {\n136\t              glog.V(3).Infof(\"auto-supersede: no prior instance at %s for %s (first-ever instance)\", priorRelPath, cmd.TaskIdentifier)\n137\t              return\n138\t          }\n139\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: read prior %s failed for %s: %v\", priorRelPath, cmd.TaskIdentifier, err)\n140\t          return\n141\t      }\n142\t      ```\n143\t      (Reuse the existing `isNotFoundReadError` helper. Transient read error → WARNING + swallow, per spec Failure Mode.)\n144\t\n145\t   e. **Parse prior frontmatter and check status (spec DB4).**\n146\t      ```go\n147\t      frontmatterStr, err := result.ExtractFrontmatter(ctx, content)\n148\t      if err != nil {\n149\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: extract frontmatter from prior %s failed for %s: %v\", priorRelPath, cmd.TaskIdentifier, err)\n150\t          return\n151\t      }\n152\t      priorFm, err := parseTaskFrontmatter(frontmatterStr)\n153\t      if err != nil {\n154\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: parse prior frontmatter %s failed for %s: %v\", priorRelPath, cmd.TaskIdentifier, err)\n155\t          return\n156\t      }\n157\t      status, _ := priorFm.String(\"status\")\n158\t      if status != \"in_progress\" {\n159\t          glog.V(3).Infof(\"auto-supersede: prior %s status=%q (not in_progress), no-op for %s\", priorRelPath, status, cmd.TaskIdentifier)\n160\t          return\n161\t      }\n162\t      ```\n163\t      (`status != \"in_progress\"` covers already-aborted/completed/done AND the Kafka-redelivery second pass — idempotent no-op.)\n164\t\n165\t   f. **Transition the prior file (spec DB5, DB6).** Build the abs path and call `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush` with a modify closure that mirrors `buildUpdateModifyFn` in `task_update_frontmatter_executor.go`:\n166\t      ```go\n167\t      ts := currentDateTime.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)\n168\t      priorAbsPath := filepath.Join(gitClient.Path(), priorRelPath)\n169\t      modify := func(current []byte) ([]byte, error) {\n170\t          fmStr, err := result.ExtractFrontmatter(ctx, current)\n171\t          if err != nil {\n172\t              return nil, errors.Wrapf(ctx, err, \"extract frontmatter\")\n173\t          }\n174\t          body, err := result.ExtractBody(ctx, current)\n175\t          if err != nil {\n176\t              return nil, errors.Wrapf(ctx, err, \"extract body\")\n177\t          }\n178\t          fm, err := parseTaskFrontmatter(fmStr)\n179\t          if err != nil {\n180\t              return nil, errors.Wrapf(ctx, err, \"parse frontmatter\")\n181\t          }\n182\t          fm[\"status\"] = \"aborted\"\n183\t          fm[\"phase\"] = \"done\"\n184\t          fm[\"completed_date\"] = ts\n185\t          fm[\"superseded_by\"] = newRelPath\n186\t          fm[\"created_by\"] = \"recurring-task-creator\"\n187\t          return marshalFileContent(ctx, fm, body)\n188\t      }\n189\t      msg := \"[agent-task-controller] auto-supersede prior recurring task \" + priorTitle\n190\t      if err := gitClient.AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPush(ctx, priorAbsPath, modify, msg); err != nil {\n191\t          glog.Warningf(\"auto-supersede: write prior %s failed for %s: %v\", priorRelPath, cmd.TaskIdentifier, err)\n192\t          return\n193\t      }\n194\t      glog.Infof(\"auto-supersede: %s -> %s (prior superseded by new instance)\", priorRelPath, newRelPath)\n195\t      ```\n196\t      - The commit message MUST contain the frozen substring `auto-supersede prior recurring task` (spec Constraint + AC). The INFO log MUST contain the frozen substring `auto-supersede:` (spec DB7).\n197\t      - The five frozen frontmatter field names — `status`, `phase`, `completed_date`, `superseded_by`, `created_by` — must be exactly these strings (spec Constraint).\n198\t      - `superseded_by` value is `newRelPath` (the new instance's repo-root-relative path), matching the AC `<taskDir>/<new title>.md`.\n199\t\n200\t   g. **Note on `newRelPath`.** The handler passes `relPath` (the resolved write path) as `newRelPath`. This is `<taskDir>/<title>.md` for the title-path case, satisfying the `superseded_by` AC.\n201\t\n202\t4. **Add the required imports** to whichever file holds `supersedePriorRecurringTask`: `\"path/filepath\"`, `\"strings\"`, `\"time\"`, `libtime \"github.com/bborbe/time\"`, `\"github.com/bborbe/errors\"`, `\"github.com/golang/glog\"`, `result \"github.com/bborbe/agent-task-controller/pkg/result\"`, `task \"github.com/bborbe/agent/command/task\"`. Several are already imported in `task_create_task_executor.go` — reuse, do not duplicate. If you create `task_supersede.go`, add only the imports that file actually uses.\n203\t\n204\t5. **Wire the clock through the factory.** In `/workspace/pkg/factory/factory.go`:\n205\t   - Add import `libtime \"github.com/bborbe/time\"`.\n206\t   - Add a `currentDateTime libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter` parameter to `CreateCommandConsumer` (append it after `vaultName string`).\n207\t   - Change the `command.NewCreateTaskExecutor(gitClient, taskDir, vaultName)` call at line 35 to `command.NewCreateTaskExecutor(gitClient, taskDir, vaultName, currentDateTime)`.\n208\t\n209\t6. **Update the `CreateCommandConsumer` call site in `/workspace/main.go`** (line 152). The local `currentDateTime` already exists at line 112. Append `currentDateTime` as the new trailing argument to the `factory.CreateCommandConsumer(...)` call. Read lines 152-162 to see the exact argument list and insert `currentDateTime` as the final argument, preserving the others in order.\n210\t\n211\t7. **Sibling entry-point check.** Run `grep -rn \"factory.CreateCommandConsumer\\|command.NewCreateTaskExecutor\" /workspace/` to confirm ALL call sites are updated. There is the production wiring in `main.go` (line 152), the factory itself, and the test harness in `pkg/command/task_create_task_executor_test.go` (which calls `command.NewCreateTaskExecutor` directly — update it per Requirement 8). If `grep` reveals any additional `main.go` variant under `cmd/` or a second `CreateCommandConsumer` caller, update it too OR document in `## Improvements` why it is out of scope. (As of writing, there is a single `main.go`; verify.)\n212\t\n213\t8. **Update existing `NewCreateTaskExecutor` test construction.** In `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor_test.go`, the `BeforeEach` constructs `executor = command.NewCreateTaskExecutor(fakeGit, taskDir, \"openclaw\")` (around line 56). Add a clock:\n214\t   - Import `libtime \"github.com/bborbe/time\"`.\n215\t   - In `BeforeEach`, create a fixed clock. Use the repo's time-injection test pattern (read `go-time-injection.md`): construct via `libtime.NewCurrentDateTime()` for a real clock, OR — to assert a deterministic `completed_date` — use a settable clock. Check `grep -rn \"SetNow\\|NewCurrentDateTimeGetter\\|ConstantCurrentDateTimeGetter\\|libtime\\.\" /workspace/pkg/ /workspace/mocks/` to find the existing settable-clock helper the codebase uses; if a settable getter exists (e.g. a counterfeiter mock or a `SetNow` method), use it so the test can assert an exact RFC 3339 value. If none exists, use `libtime.NewCurrentDateTime()` and assert `completed_date` is a non-empty, `time.RFC3339`-parseable string (spec AC requires \"non-empty RFC 3339 timestamp\").\n216\t   - Pass the clock as the new 4th argument: `command.NewCreateTaskExecutor(fakeGit, taskDir, \"openclaw\", clock)`.\n217\t   - The existing tests (malformed payload, empty TaskIdentifier, missing assignee/status, title collision) must still pass — they do not set `created_by`/`audit_style`, so the supersede hook is a no-op for them (or, for the collision case, never reached because the path returns `ErrTaskAlreadyExists` before the write).\n218\t\n219\t9. **Add the supersede unit tests** to `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor_test.go` (new `Context` blocks inside the existing `Describe(\"NewCreateTaskExecutor\")`). The mock `fakeGit.ReadFileReturns` default is a 404 (see line 56); override per-test with `ReadFileReturnsOnCall` to distinguish the title-collision read (call 0) from the prior-file read. Because the happy path issues: (read 0 = title-collision check → 404 free) then (write new via `AtomicWriteAndCommitPushStub`) then (read 1 = prior-file read), set up reads accordingly. Cover these ACs:\n220\t\n221\t   - **AC supersede happy path:** new instance frontmatter `created_by: recurring-task-creator`, no `audit_style` (or `false`), prior file read (call 1) returns content with `status: in_progress`. Assert `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount() == 1`, capture args via `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushArgsForCall(0)`, run the captured `modify` closure against the prior content, and assert the resulting bytes parse to frontmatter with `status: aborted`, `phase: done`, a non-empty RFC 3339 `completed_date`, `superseded_by == <taskDir>/<new title>.md`, `created_by: recurring-task-creator`. Also assert the captured commit message contains `auto-supersede prior recurring task`.\n222\t   - **AC audit_style true:** new instance frontmatter `created_by: recurring-task-creator`, `audit_style: true`. Assert the prior-file `ReadFile` is never issued and `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount() == 0`. (Tip: with `audit_style: true` the hook returns before any prior read; the only `ReadFile` call is the title-collision check at call 0.)\n223\t   - **AC not created by publisher:** `created_by` absent (or `created_by: someone-else`). Assert no prior `ReadFile` beyond the collision check and `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount() == 0`.\n224\t   - **AC prior not found:** eligible new instance; prior-file read (call 1) returns a 404 error (`errors.New(\"GET ... returned 404: not found\")`). Assert `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount() == 0`.\n225\t   - **AC prior status completed:** eligible; prior read returns `status: completed`. Assert no write.\n226\t   - **AC prior status aborted (redelivery 2nd pass):** eligible; prior read returns `status: aborted`. Assert no write.\n227\t   - **AC prior read non-404 error → swallowed:** eligible; prior read (call 1) returns `errors.New(\"GET ... returned 500: server error\")`. Assert `AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushCallCount() == 0` AND the handler return value is `(nil, nil, nil)` (no error returned to the caller).\n228\t   - **AC path-separator prior token:** craft a `cmd.Title` whose decremented prior title would contain a separator — since the decrementor only emits canonical tokens, instead test the slug path: use a title that decrements to a prior title containing `/`. The cleanest deterministic case: assert via a title where the slug already contains characters such that the prior title contains `/`. If the decrementor cannot produce a `/`, document this and instead assert the guard with a unit-level note; the primary path-traversal coverage is the explicit `strings.ContainsAny` guard. (Minimum: include a test where `cmd.Title` has no recognizable period token, e.g. `My Random Task`, asserting no write — covers the decrement-error + no-op branch.)\n229\t   - **AC supersede write failure swallowed:** eligible; prior read returns `status: in_progress`; set `fakeGit.AtomicReadModifyWriteAndCommitPushReturns(errors.New(\"git-rest 503\"))`. Assert the handler return value is `(nil, nil, nil)` (the write error does NOT propagate).\n230\t   - **AC superseded_by value:** assert the captured modify output's `superseded_by` equals the new instance relative path `<taskDir>/<new title>.md`.\n231\t\n232\t   For tests that need the new instance to also be written to disk via the stub, keep the existing `AtomicWriteAndCommitPushStub`. For the prior-file read, return raw markdown bytes like:\n233\t   ```\n234\t   ---\n235\t   task_identifier: prior-id\n236\t   assignee: claude\n237\t   status: in_progress\n238\t   ---\n239\t   body text\n240\t   ```\n241\t\n242\t10. **Frozen-substring grep AC.** After implementation, `grep -n 'auto-supersede prior recurring task' /workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor.go` (or `task_supersede.go` if you split it) must return ≥1 line. If you split the helper into `task_supersede.go`, the frozen commit-message substring lives there — update the AC grep target accordingly and note it in `## Improvements`.\n243\t\n244\t</requirements>\n245\t\n246\t<constraints>\n247\t\n248\t- Frozen insertion point: inside `NewCreateTaskExecutor`'s handler func, immediately after the successful `AtomicWriteAndCommitPush` and before `return nil, nil, nil`.\n249\t- Frozen git-rest client reuse: use the same `gitClient` already passed to `NewCreateTaskExecutor`. No new client, no new env var. The ONLY new constructor parameter is the clock (`libtime.CurrentDateTimeGetter`).\n250\t- Frozen frontmatter field names on the prior transition: `status`, `phase`, `completed_date`, `superseded_by`, `created_by` — do not rename.\n251\t- Frozen log substring `auto-supersede:` and frozen commit-message substring `auto-supersede prior recurring task`.\n252\t- The new instance's `audit_style` read is the sole opt-out; absence is treated as `false`. Spec Non-goal (verbatim): *\"Do NOT add a per-feature opt-out flag, config field, or tunable threshold on the controller side.\"* Do NOT add any controller-side config knob.\n253\t- The hook NEVER causes the handler to return an error — every supersede failure (decrement error, separator, read error, parse error, write error) is logged at WARNING (or V(3) for benign not-found / wrong-status) and swallowed. Handler success path stays `return nil, nil, nil`.\n254\t- The hook runs ONLY after a successful new-instance write (it is called after the `AtomicWriteAndCommitPush` block, so a failed new-instance write returns early before reaching it).\n255\t- One read, one write, no retry loop — the hook inherits the handler's context deadline (spec Security: \"must not add its own retry loop\").\n256\t- `completed_date` uses `currentDateTime.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339)` (matching `result_writer.go`).\n257\t- Do NOT add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry. Spec Non-goal (verbatim): *\"Do NOT add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry — this repo has no `CHANGELOG.md`.\"*\n258\t- Do NOT regenerate counterfeiter mocks — the `GitClient` interface is unchanged.\n259\t- Do NOT add a new E2E scenario — spec states the behavior is fully reachable via unit tests with mock `GitClient`.\n260\t- Existing tests in `/workspace/pkg/command/` and `/workspace/pkg/gitrestclient/` must still pass.\n261\t- Per `go-error-wrapping-guide.md`: `errors.Wrapf(ctx, ...)` / `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)` only — never `fmt.Errorf`, never `context.Background()` in `pkg/`.\n262\t- Per `go-precommit.md`: funlen 80 / nestif 4 / golines 100. If `supersedePriorRecurringTask` exceeds 80 lines, extract the modify-closure builder into a helper (e.g. `buildSupersedeModifyFn`).\n263\t- Do NOT commit — dark-factory handles git.\n264\t\n265\t</constraints>\n266\t\n267\t<verification>\n268\t\n269\tRun iteratively while implementing:\n270\t\n271\t```\n272\tcd /workspace && go build ./...\n273\tcd /workspace && go test ./pkg/command/... -v\n274\tcd /workspace && go test ./pkg/factory/... -v\n275\t```\n276\t\n277\tFrozen-substring check (spec AC):\n278\t\n279\t```\n280\tcd /workspace && grep -rn 'auto-supersede prior recurring task' pkg/command/\n281\t```\n282\tExpect ≥1 line.\n283\t\n284\tRun ONCE at the end:\n285\t\n286\t```\n287\tcd /workspace && make precommit\n288\t```\n289\t\n290\tExpected: exit 0; all new supersede Context specs pass (happy path, audit_style true, not-created-by-publisher, prior-not-found, prior-completed, prior-aborted, non-404-read-error swallowed, write-failure swallowed, superseded_by value, unrecognized-title no-op); existing create-task specs still pass; handler returns `(nil, nil, nil)` on every supersede failure path.\n291\t\n292\t</verification>\n293\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_5jclw9a5ulel_1","session_id":"d24d929e-901e-43de-a918-963fd3b15361","uuid":"58e12c19-39be-4d80-8884-cc8297d7bba0","timestamp":"2026-06-30T09:46:06.171Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","task_description":"Generate dark-factory prompts from spec"}
