{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WrgLnd5A5aFY6AoMY5Bct1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: executing\n3\tspec: [\"002\"]\n4\texecution_id: agent-task-controller-auto-supersede-exec-003-spec-002-period-token-decrementor\n5\tdark-factory-version: dev\n6\tcreated: \"2026-06-30T10:00:00Z\"\n7\tqueued: \"2026-06-30T09:46:00Z\"\n8\tstarted: \"2026-06-30T09:46:01Z\"\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\t<summary>\n12\t\n13\t- Adds a pure date-arithmetic helper that, given a recurring-task title like `Aquascape PWC - 2026W27`, computes the title of the prior period (`Aquascape PWC - 2026W26`).\n14\t- Recognizes six recurrence kinds purely from the shape of the period-token suffix: Daily, Weekday-list, Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Yearly.\n15\t- Correctly wraps across year boundaries (e.g. quarter `2026Q1` becomes `2025Q4`, ISO week `2026W01` becomes `2025W52`).\n16\t- Returns a clear \"unrecognized\" signal when a title has no period-token suffix, so the caller can no-op instead of guessing.\n17\t- Has zero git, network, or Kafka dependencies — it is a self-contained function exercised by table-driven unit tests at multiple anchor dates including boundary cases.\n18\t- No production behavior changes yet; this helper is consumed by the supersede hook added in prompt 2.\n19\t\n20\t</summary>\n21\t\n22\t<objective>\n23\t\n24\tAdd a pure, dependency-free helper in `pkg/command/` that decrements the period-token suffix of a recurring-task instance title to produce the prior-period title, following the durable contract in `/workspace/docs/period-token-semantics.md`. The helper recognizes the recurrence kind from the token shape (six kinds) and handles year/quarter/week boundaries. It performs no I/O. Prompt 2 consumes it.\n25\t\n26\t</objective>\n27\t\n28\t<context>\n29\t\n30\tRead `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` for project conventions.\n31\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-patterns.md` for error wrapping and naming conventions.\n32\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-error-wrapping-guide.md` for `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)` usage (never `fmt.Errorf`, never `context.Background()` in `pkg/`).\n33\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-testing-guide.md` for the Ginkgo/Gomega + table-driven layout.\n34\t\n35\tRead `/workspace/docs/period-token-semantics.md` in full — this is the durable contract this prompt implements. It defines the six token shapes, the decrement rules, the shape-recognition order, and the four named boundary cases. Implement EXACTLY this table; do not invent additional shapes.\n36\t\n37\tRead `/workspace/pkg/command/task_increment_frontmatter_executor.go` (lines 119-151) for the package's helper-function style (plain unexported funcs, `errors.Wrapf(ctx, ...)`).\n38\t\n39\tRead `/workspace/pkg/command/command_suite_test.go` — this is the Ginkgo suite bootstrap for `package command_test`. New `_test.go` files in this package use `package command_test` and the `. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"` / `. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"` dot-imports (see `task_create_task_executor_test.go` lines 1-22 for the exact import block).\n40\t\n41\tContract recap from `/workspace/docs/period-token-semantics.md` (implement verbatim):\n42\t\n43\t| Recurrence kind | Token shape (new) | Decrement rule |\n44\t|---|---|---|\n45\t| Daily | `YYYY-MM-DD` | one calendar day before |\n46\t| Weekday (list) | `YYYYWww-<3-letter-abbrev>` | one ISO week before; abbrev preserved (`2026W27-sat` → `2026W26-sat`) |\n47\t| Weekly | `YYYYWww` | one ISO week before (`2026W27` → `2026W26`) |\n48\t| Monthly | `YYYY-MM` | one calendar month before (`2026-06` → `2026-05`) |\n49\t| Quarterly | `YYYYQq` | one quarter before; wrap `Q1` → prior-year `Q4` |\n50\t| Yearly | `YYYY` | one calendar year before |\n51\t\n52\tShape-recognition order (try in this exact order): Daily, Weekday, Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Yearly.\n53\t\n54\tBoundary cases that MUST pass: Quarterly `2026Q1 → 2025Q4`; Weekly `2026W01 → 2025W52`; Monthly `2026-01 → 2025-12`; Daily `2026-01-01 → 2025-12-31`; Weekday `2026W01-mon → 2025W52-mon`.\n55\t\n56\t</context>\n57\t\n58\t<requirements>\n59\t\n60\t1. **Create `/workspace/pkg/command/period_token_decrementor.go`** in `package command` with the standard BSD license header (copy the 3-line header from `/workspace/pkg/command/task_create_task_executor.go` lines 1-3).\n61\t\n62\t2. **Implement the title-splitting and decrement entry point.** Define an unexported function with this exact signature:\n63\t   ```go\n64\t   // decrementRecurringTaskTitle splits title into its slug prefix and period-token\n65\t   // suffix on the final \" - \" separator, decrements the token to the prior period\n66\t   // per docs/period-token-semantics.md, and returns \"<slug> - <prior-token>\".\n67\t   // It returns an error if the title has no \" - <token>\" suffix or the token suffix\n68\t   // matches none of the six recognized shapes (caller must no-op on error).\n69\t   func decrementRecurringTaskTitle(ctx context.Context, title string) (string, error)\n70\t   ```\n71\t   - Split on the LAST occurrence of the literal separator `\" - \"` (space-hyphen-space). Use `strings.LastIndex(title, \" - \")`. If not found, return `\"\", errors.Errorf(ctx, \"title %q has no period-token suffix\", title)`.\n72\t   - The part before the separator is the slug; the part after is the raw token. Reconstruct as `slug + \" - \" + priorToken`.\n73\t   - Slug may itself contain `\" - \"` (e.g. a title `Foo - Bar - 2026W27` → slug `Foo - Bar`, token `2026W27`) — LastIndex handles this correctly.\n74\t\n75\t3. **Implement the per-shape decrement.** Define an unexported function:\n76\t   ```go\n77\t   // decrementPeriodToken returns the prior-period token for a single period-token\n78\t   // string, recognizing the kind by shape (order per docs/period-token-semantics.md).\n79\t   func decrementPeriodToken(ctx context.Context, token string) (string, error)\n80\t   ```\n81\t   Recognition order and rules:\n82\t   1. **Daily** — `YYYY-MM-DD`. Match with `regexp.MustCompile(`^(\\d{4})-(\\d{2})-(\\d{2})$`)`. Parse with `time.Parse(\"2006-01-02\", token)`, subtract one day via `t.AddDate(0, 0, -1)`, format back with `t.Format(\"2006-01-02\")`.\n83\t   2. **Weekday (list)** — `YYYYWww-<3-letter-abbrev>`. Match `^(\\d{4})W(\\d{2})-([a-z]{3})$`. Decrement the `YYYYWww` ISO-week part by one ISO week (see step 3's algorithm) and re-append `-<abbrev>` unchanged. The abbrev is preserved verbatim.\n84\t   3. **Weekly** — `YYYYWww`. Match `^(\\d{4})W(\\d{2})$`. To decrement one ISO week:\n85\t      - Parse the ISO year and week ints from the two capture groups (`strconv.Atoi`).\n86\t      - Construct a `time.Time` for the Monday of that ISO week. Go's stdlib has no direct ISO-week constructor; compute it by: take `time.Date(isoYear, 1, 4, 0,0,0,0, time.UTC)` (Jan 4 is always in ISO week 1), find that week's Monday, then add `(week-1)*7` days. Subtract 7 days to move to the prior ISO week.\n87\t      - Read the prior week's canonical ISO year+week via `prior.ISOWeek()`, then format as `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04dW%02d\", py, pw)`. This yields the correct `2026W01 → 2025W52` wrap because `ISOWeek()` returns the canonical ISO year.\n88\t   4. **Monthly** — `YYYY-MM`. Match `^(\\d{4})-(\\d{2})$`. Parse with `time.Parse(\"2006-01\", token)`, subtract one month via `t.AddDate(0, -1, 0)`, format with `t.Format(\"2006-01\")`. (`2026-01 → 2025-12` follows from `AddDate`.)\n89\t   5. **Quarterly** — `YYYYQq` where `q` is `1`-`4`. Match `^(\\d{4})Q([1-4])$`. Decrement: if `q > 1` → `(year, q-1)`; if `q == 1` → `(year-1, 4)`. Format `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04dQ%d\", year, q)`.\n90\t   6. **Yearly** — `YYYY`. Match `^(\\d{4})$`. Parse year, subtract one, format `fmt.Sprintf(\"%04d\", year-1)`.\n91\t   - If NONE match, return `\"\", errors.Errorf(ctx, \"period token %q matches no recognized shape\", token)`.\n92\t   - Compile each regexp once at package scope (`var dailyRe = regexp.MustCompile(...)` etc.) — do NOT compile inside the function (lint + perf).\n93\t\n94\t4. **Ordering correctness for Daily vs Monthly vs Yearly.** Because `YYYY-MM-DD`, `YYYY-MM`, and `YYYY` are distinct anchored regexps (`^...$`), order matters only between overlapping shapes; the anchored patterns are mutually exclusive, so checking in the documented order is safe. Still, follow the documented order literally (Daily → Weekday → Weekly → Monthly → Quarterly → Yearly) so the code matches the contract doc one-to-one.\n95\t\n96\t5. **Do NOT add path-separator rejection here.** Path-traversal defense on the computed prior token lives in the supersede hook (prompt 2), not in this pure helper. This helper only does date arithmetic on token strings.\n97\t\n98\t6. **Create `/workspace/pkg/command/period_token_decrementor_test.go`** in `package command_test` with a table-driven Ginkgo spec. Because the test lives in an external package, the unexported `decrementRecurringTaskTitle` is not directly accessible — export a thin test seam OR test through the supersede hook. Use this approach: add an `export_test.go`-style seam. Create `/workspace/pkg/command/export_test.go` (if it does not already exist; check with `ls /workspace/pkg/command/export_test.go`) in `package command` exposing:\n99\t   ```go\n100\t   // Test-only re-exports for the external command_test package.\n101\t   var DecrementRecurringTaskTitle = decrementRecurringTaskTitle\n102\t   ```\n103\t   If `export_test.go` already exists, append the var to it instead of overwriting. Then the test calls `command.DecrementRecurringTaskTitle(ctx, title)`.\n104\t\n105\t7. **Table-driven test rows.** Cover all six kinds at ≥2 anchor dates each, INCLUDING the boundary case for that kind, so a hardcoded lookup keyed on exact test strings cannot satisfy the test. Minimum rows (newTitle → expected priorTitle):\n106\t   - Daily mid-year: `Cleanup Inbox - 2026-06-15` → `Cleanup Inbox - 2026-06-14`\n107\t   - Daily year-boundary: `Cleanup Inbox - 2026-01-01` → `Cleanup Inbox - 2025-12-31`\n108\t   - Weekday mid-year: `Standup - 2026W27-sat` → `Standup - 2026W26-sat`\n109\t   - Weekday year-boundary: `Standup - 2026W01-mon` → `Standup - 2025W52-mon`\n110\t   - Weekly mid-year: `Aquascape PWC - 2026W27` → `Aquascape PWC - 2026W26`\n111\t   - Weekly ISO-week year-boundary: `Aquascape PWC - 2026W01` → `Aquascape PWC - 2025W52`\n112\t   - Monthly mid-year: `Pay Rent - 2026-06` → `Pay Rent - 2026-05`\n113\t   - Monthly year-boundary: `Pay Rent - 2026-01` → `Pay Rent - 2025-12`\n114\t   - Quarterly mid-year: `Quarterly Review - 2026Q2` → `Quarterly Review - 2026Q1`\n115\t   - Quarterly year-boundary: `Quarterly Review - 2026Q1` → `Quarterly Review - 2025Q4`\n116\t   - Yearly: `Annual Filing - 2026` → `Annual Filing - 2025`\n117\t   - Yearly boundary (decade): `Annual Filing - 2020` → `Annual Filing - 2019`\n118\t   - Slug containing the separator: `Foo - Bar - 2026W27` → `Foo - Bar - 2026W26`\n119\t   For each row assert `command.DecrementRecurringTaskTitle(ctx, newTitle)` returns the expected prior title and a nil error.\n120\t\n121\t8. **Error-path test rows** (separate `It` blocks or table with `expectErr bool`):\n122\t   - No suffix separator: `RandomTask` → error (no `\" - \"`).\n123\t   - Unrecognized token shape: `Weird Task - notaperiod` → error (matches no shape).\n124\t   - Empty token after separator: `Bad - ` → error.\n125\t   For each, assert the returned error is non-nil.\n126\t\n127\t9. **Use `ctx := context.Background()` in tests** (the standard test-suite context). Production callers pass the handler context; the helper only uses `ctx` to wrap errors.\n128\t\n129\t</requirements>\n130\t\n131\t<constraints>\n132\t\n133\t- Implement EXACTLY the six shapes in `/workspace/docs/period-token-semantics.md` — no extra shapes, no opt-out flags, no config. Spec Non-goal (verbatim): *\"Do NOT add a per-feature opt-out flag, config field, or tunable threshold on the controller side.\"*\n134\t- This helper has ZERO I/O — no git, no Kafka, no filesystem, no clock. It is pure date arithmetic on strings.\n135\t- Per `go-error-wrapping-guide.md`: errors wrap with `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)` / `errors.Wrapf(ctx, err, ...)` from `github.com/bborbe/errors` — never `fmt.Errorf`, never `context.Background()` inside `pkg/`.\n136\t- Per `go-precommit.md`: file-level lint limits (funlen 80, nestif 4, golines 100). Keep `decrementPeriodToken` under 80 lines — if it approaches the limit, extract per-kind helpers (`decrementWeek`, `decrementQuarter`).\n137\t- Do NOT add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry. Spec Non-goal (verbatim): *\"Do NOT add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry — this repo has no `CHANGELOG.md`.\"*\n138\t- Compile regexps at package scope, not inside functions.\n139\t- Existing tests in `/workspace/pkg/command/` must still pass.\n140\t- Do NOT commit — dark-factory handles git.\n141\t\n142\t</constraints>\n143\t\n144\t<verification>\n145\t\n146\tRun iteratively while implementing:\n147\t\n148\t```\n149\tcd /workspace && go build ./pkg/command/...\n150\tcd /workspace && go test ./pkg/command/... -v\n151\t```\n152\t\n153\tRun ONCE at the end:\n154\t\n155\t```\n156\tcd /workspace && make precommit\n157\t```\n158\t\n159\tExpected: all period-token table rows pass, including the four named boundary cases (`2026Q1 → 2025Q4`, `2026W01 → 2025W52`, `2026-01 → 2025-12`, `2026-01-01 → 2025-12-31`); error rows return non-nil errors; `make precommit` exits 0.\n160\t\n161\t</verification>\n162\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_2tkioin7gykw_1","session_id":"d24d929e-901e-43de-a918-963fd3b15361","uuid":"89fc290c-95be-49b6-a30a-c1878cd249e9","timestamp":"2026-06-30T09:48:45.787Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-auditor","task_description":"Audit prompt 1 - period-token decrementor"}
